    "One interesting difference between DNN and RF is the change in behavior of substructure-based fingerprints: while they generally lead to high recall for RF, they have more diverse performance when using DNNs.",
    "For example, PubChem here scores highly in precision, while ESTATE maintains high recall instead (Fig. 4c and d).",
    "One notable similarity between RF and DNN is that both have good performance with the MHFP fingerprint (Additional file 1: Figure S6).",
